'''Cristian Jesús Martínez''' (born 6 February 1997) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Israeli Premier League]] club [[Hapoel Ironi Kiryat Shmona F.C.|Ironi Kiryat Shmona]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
===Chorrillo===
Martínez joined the youth team of his local side [[Chorrillo F.C.|Chorrillo]] at the age of 8, eventually joining the club's first team in 2012.

===Columbus Crew===
Martínez signed on loan with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Columbus Crew]] on 17 May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/05/17/columbus-crew-sc-add-wing-depth-panama-teenager-cristian-martinez |title=Columbus Crew SC add to wing depth with Panama teenager Cristian Martinez |website=MLSsoccer.com |date= |accessdate=2016-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.massivereport.com/2016/5/17/11691312/crew-sc-sign-panamanian-cristian-martinez-to-loan-deal |title=Crew SC sign Panamanian Cristian Martinez to loan deal |publisher=Massive Report |date=17 May 2016 |accessdate=2016-05-20 |archive-date=2 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802145902/http://www.massivereport.com/2016/5/17/11691312/crew-sc-sign-panamanian-cristian-martinez-to-loan-deal |url-status=dead }}</ref> Martínez made his MLS debut on June 1, 2016, coming on as a substitute in a 3–2 loss to [[Philadelphia Union]]. He scored in the 90+3', becoming the youngest Crew SC goal scorer in a regular-season match in club history.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://matchcenter.columbuscrewsc.com/matchcenter/2016-06-01-philadelphia-union-vs-columbus-crew-sc/feed |title=Columbus Crew SC vs. Philadelphia Union |website=ColumbusCrewSC.com |accessdate=23 December 2016 |archive-date=2019-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321155437/https://matchcenter.columbuscrewsc.com/matchcenter/2016-06-01-philadelphia-union-vs-columbus-crew-sc/feed |url-status=dead }}</ref> Martínez would be loaned by Crew SC to [[Pittsburgh Riverhounds]], the club's [[United Soccer League|USL]] affiliate. He made his Riverhounds debut against [[FC Montreal]] on 10 August 2016. Crew SC would recall Martínez for two more appearances at the end of the MLS season. On 25 January,  Martínez was acquired on a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbuscrewsc.com/post/2017/01/25/news-crew-sc-signs-us-youth-international-obinwa-completes-permanent-transfer |title=NEWS: Crew SC signs U.S. Youth international Obinwa, completes permanent transfer for Martinez |website=columbuscrewsc.com |date= |accessdate=2017-01-25}}</ref> On May 4, 2017, Martínez was loaned to [[United Soccer League]] club [[FC Cincinnati (2016–18)|FC Cincinnati]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fccincinnati.com/news_article/show/789083|title=FCC Signs Crew's Cristian Martinez|last=Kimura|first=Fumi|date=May 5, 2017|publisher=[[FC Cincinnati (2016–18)|FC Cincinnati]]|accessdate=May 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512062639/http://www.fccincinnati.com/news_article/show/789083|archive-date=May 12, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> He played in one game before returning to the Columbus Crew on May 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cincinnati.com/story/sports/soccer/fc-cincinnati/2017/05/08/update-fc-cincinnatis-roster/101441948/|title=Update on FC Cincinnati's roster|last=Brennan|first=Patrick|date=May 8, 2017|work=[[The Cincinnati Enquirer]]|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref>

===Chicago Fire===
On 12 December 2018, Martínez was selected by [[Chicago Fire SC|Chicago Fire]] in the MLS Waiver Draft.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chicago-fire.com/post/2018/12/12/chicago-fire-soccer-club-selects-midfielder-cristian-mart-nez-forward-marco-ure-2018|title=Chicago Fire Soccer Club Selects Midfielder Cristian Martínez, Forward Marco Ureña in 2018 MLS Waiver Draft &#124; Chicago Fire FC}}</ref>

On 24 August 2019, Martínez joined [[USL Championship]] side [[Las Vegas Lights FC|Las Vegas Lights]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uslchampionship.com/news_article/show/1043915|title=Lights FC Adds Martinez on Loan from Fire|date=23 August 2019}}</ref>

===Cádiz===
On January 18, 2020, [[Cádiz CF]] announced his signing until 2022 and that he would be loaned to a [[Segunda División B]] team. On January 24 it was made official that that team would be [[Recreativo de Huelva]].

On January 30, 2021, [[Cádiz CF]] announced his six-month loan to [[C.D. Plaza Amador|CD Plaza Amador]] of Panama.

===Najran===
On 20 January 2023, Martínez joined Saudi Arabian club [[Najran SC|Najran]].<ref>{{cite web |title=أنهت إدارة نادي #نجران إجراءات التعاقد مع المحور البنمي الدولي "كريستيان مارتينيز |url=https://twitter.com/MC_NajranFC/status/1616502691336790016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Cristian Martínez jugará en Arabia Saudita con Najran SC |date=20 January 2023 |url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/cristian-martinez-jugara-arabia-saudita-najran-sc-n5834388}}</ref>

===Plaza Amador===
On 26 July 2023, Martínez joined [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]].<ref>{{cite web |title=LPF: Plaza Amador se refuerza con "Fulo" Cristian Martínez |date=26 July 2023 |url=https://www.rpctv.com/liga-panamena-futbol-lpf/futbol/lpf-plaza-amador-se-refuerza-fulo-cristian-martinez-n5905165}}</ref>

===Al-Jandal===
On 16 September 2023, Martínez joined Saudi Arabian club [[Al Jandal SC|Al-Jandal]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الدولي البنمي كريستيان مارتينيز جندلاوي |url=https://twitter.com/Aljandal_Fc/status/1703119374293377098}}</ref>

===Ironi Kiryat Shmona===
On 13 July 2024 signed for the Israeli club [[Hapoel Ironi Kiryat Shmona F.C.|Ironi Kiryat Shmona]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.one.co.il/Article/23-24/1,1,3112,49596/467633.html?ref=hp|title= קשר נבחרת פנמה חתם בעירוני קריית שמונה|first= Tomer|last= Habaz|date= 2024-07-13|accessdate= 2024-07-13|publisher= ONE|language= HE}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2018 he was named in Panama's preliminary 35 man [[Panama national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists - Goal.com|website=www.goal.com}}</ref> However, he did not make the final 23.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/panama/story/3513736/panamas-final-world-cup-squad-includes-six-mls-players|title=Panama's final squad includes 6 MLS players|date=30 May 2018|website=ESPN.com}}</ref>

